  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca 3057\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0 \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0d86\u0dba\u0dad\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A company that used 3057 tons of rice for animal feed production was raided",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A raid has been conducted in relation to the use of imported rice in an animal feed manufacturing company located in Kinagaspitiya area of \u200b\u200bKurunegala, where officials have taken into custody a stock of 3057 metric tons of rice in 25/50 kg packing bags.",
        "The Consumer Affairs Authority has issued a gazette notice on 24.06.2022 prohibiting the use of rice for animal feed. Accordingly, a special raid investigation program has been started from yesterday i.e. 30.07.2022 in relation to establishments that use rice for animal feed.",
        "According to the information of the production manager, there were 125 bags of 25 kg in the lorries. The raid was carried out by the officers of the Kurunegala Consumer Affairs Authority and they are going to be presented to the Kurunegala Magistrate's Court on 08-05-2022 under the charge of storing rice to be used for animal feed. ) was completed around 3.10 pm.",
        "The consumer affairs authority requests traders not to use rice for animal feed and not to supply rice for that purpose."
      ],
